text: Donegal Creek is a U.S. Geological Survey. National Hydrography Dataset high- resolution flowline data. The National Map, accessed March 24, 2019 tributary of Chiques Creek in Lancaster County, Pennsylvania in the United States. The stream rises from Donegal Springs in East Donegal Township. Donegal Creek joins Chiques Creek upstream of the Susquehanna River. ==See also== *List of rivers of Pennsylvania ==References== Category:Rivers of Pennsylvania Category:Tributaries of the Susquehanna River Category:Rivers of Lancaster County, Pennsylvania
